A salesman, Joseph Omoniyi, yesterday appeared at a Surulere Chief Magistrates’ Court for allegedly stealing his employer’s N650,000. Omoniyi, 36, pleaded not guilty. Prosecuting Inspector Rukayat Ogundeji said the defendant committed the offence from  last October to December at Foyaf Investment Company Ltd, Lagos. She alleged that the defendant sold some items worth N650, 000 and fraudulently converted the money to his use. Chief Magistrate T.O. Abayomi granted the defendant N250, 000 bail with two sureties in the like sum. She said the sureties must be employed and show evidence of tax payments to the Lagos State Government. The case was adjourned till May 28.